('professor', 'Catachresis refers to ___.', '["A. correct grammar", "B. strained or improper metaphor", "C. metrical feet", "D. IPA notation"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '誤喻為不當或過度延伸隱喻。'),
('professor', 'Synecdoche uses ___.', '["A. rhyme", "B. a part for the whole or vice versa", "C. homophones", "D. palindrome"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '提喻以部分代整體或反之。'),
('professor', 'Litotes expresses affirmation through ___.', '["A. hyperbole", "B. double negation or understatement", "C. simile", "D. allusion"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '曲言法以否定或輕描淡寫表肯定。'),
('professor', 'Pejorative connotation means the word feels ___.', '["A. neutral", "B. positive", "C. negative", "D. technical"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '貶義為負面色彩。'),
('professor', 'If an argument affirms the consequent, it is ___.', '["A. valid", "B. sound", "C. formally invalid", "D. inductive only"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '肯定後件為形式謬誤。'),
('professor', 'Denying the antecedent is ___.', '["A. always valid", "B. formally invalid", "C. the same as modus ponens", "D. a strong analogy"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '否定前件為無效推論。'),
('professor', 'A deductively valid argument can still be ___.', '["A. unsound if premises are false", "B. always sound", "C. inductive", "D. self-refuting always"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '有效論證若前提假仍可 unsound。'),
('professor', 'An ad hoc rescue revises a theory ___.', '["A. before testing", "B. only to protect it from falsification", "C. using statistics only", "D. through translation"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '特設性防衛為免於被否證而補救。'),
('professor', 'Straw man fallacy involves ___.', '["A. using analogies", "B. misrepresenting an opponent''s view", "C. appealing to pity", "D. equivocation only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '稻草人謬誤扭曲對方論點。'),
('professor', 'Equivocation shifts ___.', '["A. tenses", "B. the meaning of a key term", "C. font size", "D. sample size"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '歧義謬誤偷換關鍵詞義。'),
('professor', 'Post hoc ergo propter hoc mistakes ___.', '["A. correlation for authentication", "B. sequence for causation", "C. cause for correlation", "D. definition for example"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '後此謬誤把先後當因果。'),
('professor', 'Begging the question ___.', '["A. asks politely", "B. assumes the conclusion in premises", "C. uses only empirical data", "D. avoids pronouns"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '循環論證把結論藏於前提。'),
('professor', 'The word ''otiose'' most nearly means ___.', '["A. meticulous", "B. superfluous", "C. rapid", "D. fragrant"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'otiose 意為多餘、無用。'),
('professor', 'The word ''perspicacious'' suggests ___.', '["A. sloppy thinking", "B. keen insight", "C. physical strength", "D. anger"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'perspicacious 表示敏銳洞察。'),
('professor', 'The word ''recalcitrant'' fits ___.', '["A. a willing volunteer", "B. a stubborn resistor", "C. a transparent liquid", "D. a cheap fabric"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'recalcitrant 形容頑抗不服。'),
('professor', 'The word ''sycophant'' denotes ___.', '["A. a wise teacher", "B. a servile flatterer", "C. a neutral judge", "D. a brave pioneer"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'sycophant 為阿諛奉承者。'),
('professor', 'The word ''laconic'' describes speech that is ___.', '["A. lengthy", "B. brief", "C. loud", "D. archaic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'laconic 表示簡潔寡言。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''to pull someone''s leg'' means ___.', '["A. to help them walk", "B. to tease or joke", "C. to betray them", "D. to lend money"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '英式幽默表示開玩笑、捉弄。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''bury the hatchet'' means ___.', '["A. hide tools", "B. make peace", "C. start a fight", "D. plant trees"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '言歸於好、止息爭端。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''let sleeping dogs lie'' advises ___.', '["A. wake pets", "B. avoid stirring up trouble", "C. train animals", "D. sleep more"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '勿挑起不必要的麻煩。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''the ball is in your court'' means ___.', '["A. play tennis", "B. it''s your turn to act", "C. you lost", "D. the game ended"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '輪到你採取行動。'),
('professor', 'The idiom ''cut corners'' suggests ___.', '["A. meticulous work", "B. doing something hastily or improperly", "C. taking a shortcut road only", "D. building squares"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '偷工減料、走捷徑敷衍。'),
('professor', 'An oxymoron pairs ___.', '["A. synonyms", "B. contradictory terms", "C. foreign words", "D. rhyming words"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '矛盾修辭並置相反概念。'),
('professor', 'Epistemic modality expresses ___.', '["A. obligation about the past", "B. speaker''s degree of commitment to truth", "C. physical ability only", "D. future tense only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '認識情態表說話者對命題真假的確信度。'),
('professor', 'Deictic expressions depend on ___.', '["A. Latin roots", "B. utterance context", "C. metrical stress", "D. silent letters"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '指示詞依賴語境座標。'),
('professor', 'A minimal pair in phonology demonstrates ___.', '["A. free variation", "B. phonemic contrast", "C. allophony only", "D. tone sandhi"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '最小對立組顯示音位對立。'),
('professor', 'Complementary distribution typically indicates ___.', '["A. phonemes", "B. allophones of one phoneme", "C. minimal pairs", "D. word stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '互補分布多為同一音位之變體。'),
('professor', 'The passive voice is sometimes preferred in scientific writing to ___.', '["A. increase wordiness", "B. foreground the process or result", "C. avoid verbs", "D. hide subject always"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '被動可突出過程或結果。'),
('professor', 'The rhetorical question primarily functions to ___.', '["A. request information only", "B. prompt reflection rather than an answer", "C. change tense", "D. translate literally"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '反問用於引發思考而非真問。'),
('professor', 'Pathos appeals to ___.', '["A. logic", "B. credibility", "C. emotion", "D. grammar"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '悲情訴諸情感 pathos。'),
('professor', 'Logos appeals to ___.', '["A. emotion", "B. character", "C. reasoning and evidence", "D. rhythm"]'::jsonb, 'C', 2, '理性訴諸論證 logos。'),
('professor', 'Ethos appeals to ___.', '["A. statistics only", "B. speaker credibility", "C. musicality", "D. imagery only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '人格訴諸可信度 ethos。'),
('professor', 'Ambiguity of scope may confuse whether ___.', '["A. a verb is transitive", "B. negation applies to one clause or another", "C. nouns are plural", "D. letters are silent"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '範域歧義影響否定範圍。'),
('professor', 'Vagueness differs from ambiguity because vagueness ___.', '["A. has two precise senses", "B. involves borderline cases", "C. is always grammatical", "D. requires synonyms"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '模糊涉及界線案例而非雙義。'),
('professor', 'Performative utterances ___.', '["A. cannot be spoken", "B. do something by being said", "C. only describe weather", "D. lack verbs"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '施為句以說出即完成行為。'),
('professor', 'Implicature (Gricean) relies on ___.', '["A. literal grammar only", "B. conversational cooperation and context", "C. spelling rules", "D. IPA charts"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '含意依合作原則與語境推導。'),
('professor', 'A malapropism is ___.', '["A. a deliberate pun", "B. an amusing word substitution error", "C. a silent letter", "D. a dialect map"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '誤用近似音詞造成滑稽效果。'),
('professor', 'Proprioceptive imagery appeals to ___.', '["A. sight", "B. internal bodily sensation", "C. hearing", "D. taste only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '本體感覺意象描寫身體內部感覺。'),
('professor', 'Synesthesia in literature ___.', '["A. avoids metaphor", "B. crosses sensory domains", "C. uses only facts", "D. removes adjectives"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '通感跨感官域。'),
('professor', 'The hedging phrase ''I might be wrong, but...'' serves to ___.', '["A. assert certainty", "B. soften the claim", "C. change topic", "D. quote sources"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '模糊限制語弱化斷言。'),
('professor', 'Parallelism in prose primarily enhances ___.', '["A. confusion", "B. rhythm and clarity", "C. spelling", "D. font choice"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '排比增節奏與清晰度。'),
('professor', 'Antimetabole repeats words in ___.', '["A. random order", "B. reverse order", "C. alphabetical order", "D. silent letters"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '逆序重複為 antimetabole。'),
('professor', 'The pathetic fallacy attributes human emotion to ___.', '["A. numbers", "B. nature or objects", "C. verbs only", "D. footnotes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '感情誤置賦予自然或物情感。'),
('professor', 'An enthymeme in rhetoric is ___.', '["A. a long poem", "B. a syllogism with an unstated premise", "C. a type of irony", "D. a grammar rule"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '省略三段論省略前提。'),
('professor', 'The distinction between ''fewer'' and ''less'' is prescriptively about ___.', '["A. formality", "B. count vs mass nouns", "C. British vs American", "D. past vs present"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '規範上 fewer 配可數、less 配不可數。'),
('professor', 'In philosophy of language, ''extension'' of a term is ___.', '["A. its intension", "B. the set of things it denotes", "C. its etymology", "D. its pronunciation"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '外延為詞所指對象集合。'),
('professor', 'The intension of a word includes ___.', '["A. only pronunciation", "B. associative or definitional properties", "C. only spelling", "D. rhyme scheme"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '內涵為定義性質與屬性。'),
('professor', 'If P implies Q, then ''not Q'' implies ___.', '["A. P", "B. not P", "C. Q", "D. P and Q"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '拒取式：非 Q 則非 P（假設原為 P→Q）。'),
('professor', 'A contingent truth is one that ___.', '["A. must be true in all worlds", "B. could have been otherwise", "C. is self-contradictory", "D. only concerns math"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '偶然真理可以不是如此。'),
('professor', 'Analytic statements are often characterized as ___.', '["A. empirical", "B. true by virtue of meaning", "C. always false", "D. poetic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '分析句依意義為真。'),
('professor', 'Synthetic statements ___.', '["A. are true by definition only", "B. combine concepts not contained in the subject", "C. cannot be false", "D. lack predicates"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '綜合句把主詞所無之概念連結起來。'),
('professor', 'The fallacy of composition assumes ___.', '["A. parts equal whole properties", "B. what is true of parts is true of the whole", "C. correlation implies causation", "D. experts are wrong"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '合成謬誤以部分性質推整體。'),
('professor', 'The fallacy of division assumes ___.', '["A. the whole''s property belongs to every part", "B. correlation is causation", "C. samples are random", "D. definitions shift"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '分割謬誤以整體屬性推每一部分。'),
('professor', 'A virtue of a clear operational definition is that it ___.', '["A. avoids all measurement", "B. makes variables observable and testable", "C. removes ethics", "D. eliminates theory"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '操作型定義使變項可觀測檢驗。'),
('professor', 'In academic hedging, the verb suggests is weaker than ___.', '["A. might", "B. proves", "C. could", "D. may"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'suggests 比 proves 語氣弱。');
